But, talking about the PCI, altrought this is a GOOD step fo Amiga,
i can't agree that AGP 4x don't bring us notably improve of GFX writing
speed (writing into GFX ram...) over the PCI. Well, only for 604e+, but
does.

But i want write something diferent. I'm not so sure, if the PCI
implementations does not lost with the real world battle with the Z3 bus,
after all. Why and what BS i talking about? Easy to understand, dudes.
Technicaly speaking, PCI (as Z2, for example!) is a SYNCHRON bus, what
also means, that during writing, the CPU is (it must!) be locked for
ensuring the determined (SYNCHRON) speed of writing. That is GOOD for
test's, but into reality it does not performs that good, just because
loacking a CPU cause, that CPU can't prepare next data or just do
anything other. The Z3 slots are driven mainly by the Buster 11 chip,
so the CPU is not too much involved during the writing, so therefore
when you make a benchmark of movies playback, for example, the Z3 with
decent card (PIV, not the CV3D, that is NOT a decent card...!) win
over the - on tests faster - CVPPC easily.

Unfortunately, we can't afford staing oposite to whole world (no matter
how stupid it might looks for some of us) and making own GFX chips and
cards, because thats are too much expensive...

So, the PCI is a very good solution for us anyway!
